Male actor, 25-40 years old, wanted.

You should be good-looking and well-built and not afraid of queer parts.

I'm an actor from Germany and from time to time I also make short films, which I present at international film festivals .

My films are arthouse films that may contain nudity and improvisation.

My upcoming short will be an online romance.

The actor should therefore record their part at home using their own smartphone.

Unfortunately, there's no payment, but it only takes 1-2 days. Sorry,  It's not possible to make money with a short film.
Filming will be in English.

I'm also looking for actors for potential future projects.

This is me: www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Please write to Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de

**The Revolution of Independent Film Starts Here.**

Atlanta isn‚Äôt just the backdrop, it‚Äôs the heartbeat.

Home to a **$4.1 billion film industry**, thousands of indie filmmakers, and stories that refuse to wait for permission.

This December, the **Atlanta Auteur Film Festival & Film Market** turns the spotlight on the creators redefining Georgia‚Äôs cinematic identity.

40 short films that speak truth.
Workshops that build futures.
Deals that keep creativity in motion.

It‚Äôs raw. It‚Äôs real. It‚Äôs *Auteur.*

**December 6, 2025** | **Riverside EpiCenter**

Tickets, submissions, vendor and sponsorship info: auteuratlanta.com

#AtlantaAuteur #IndieFilm #GeorgiaFilm #FilmMarket #CreatorsUnite #SupportIndieCinema #AuteurAtlanta

Casting Call: Singer-Songwriter for Music Video (Unpaid)

Production Title: Christmas Music video 
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.
Type: Music Video
Location: Colorado (exact location TBD)
Filming Dates: late November early December 2025
Compensation: Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

---

About the Project

Superstar TV Entertainment Inc. is producing a heartfelt, cinematic music video featuring a singer-songwriter whose performance captures raw emotion and authenticity. This project is designed to highlight both the artist and visual storytelling ‚Äî similar in tone to Lewis Capaldi, Adele, or Noah Kahan.

The final video will be professionally shot and released across Superstar TV platforms, YouTube, and social media for maximum exposure.

---

Roles

üé§ Lead Artist / Singer-Songwriter (Principal Role)

Gender: Open to all

Age Range: 18‚Äì35

Vocal Style: Pop, acoustic, R&B, soul, or indie-folk preferred

Description: Emotionally expressive performer with on-camera presence. Must be comfortable lip-syncing to playback or performing live vocals. Guitar or piano ability is a plus.

Requirements: Must be reliable, punctual, and open to creative collaboration.

---

Supporting Roles (If applicable)

Love Interest: Ages 20‚Äì35, expressive and able to convey emotional connection.

Extras: Audience members, friends, or background talent for performance scenes.

---

Compensation

Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

You‚Äôll receive:

A professional-quality music video for your reel

IMDB credit under Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.

Networking opportunity for future paid productions

---

Submission Instructions

Please submit the following to tyler.schachtceo@outlook.com with the subject line:
Christmas Music Video ‚Äì [Your Name]‚Äù

Include:

Headshot or clear photo

Short performance clip or demo reel (YouTube or social media link accepted)

Short bio or resume

Contact information (email + phone number)

**S√òGER DELTAGERE TIL DOKUMENTAR**

Vi er to filmskabere fra **Potemkin, den jyske filmskole**, der skal til at lave deres afgangsprojekt ‚Äî en smuk, poetisk mini-dokumentar med titlen *Med d√∏den p√• forkant*.

Filmen handler om, hvordan d√∏den kan komme f√∏r tiden ‚Äî og hvordan man lever videre, n√•r nogen forsvinder alt for tidligt. Vi √∏nsker at skabe et stille, √¶rligt og visuelt poetisk portr√¶t af k√¶rligheden og savnet, n√•r livet bliver afbrudt midt i det smukkeste.

For hvordan f√∏les det, n√•r d√∏den kommer p√• forkant?
N√•r man ikke bare savner en person, men ogs√• alt det, personen aldrig n√•ede at opleve?

Vi s√∏ger derfor tre personer, der har oplevet at miste **alt for tidligt**:
* en, der har mistet en **for√¶lder** i en ung alder
* en, der har mistet et **barn**
* og en, der har mistet sin **partner / √¶gtef√¶lle** f√∏r tiden

Optagelserne vil foreg√• i trygge rammer, og vi l√¶gger stor v√¶gt p√• respekt, n√¶rv√¶r og tillid i processen. Vi √∏nsker at skabe en film, der viser sorgen ‚Äì men ogs√• k√¶rligheden, styrken og de sm√• spor, der bliver tilbage.

Hvis du har lyst til at dele din historie ‚Äì eller bare vil h√∏re mere om projektet ‚Äì er du meget velkommen til at skrive til mig p√• denne mail: [sara774g@gmail.com](mailto:sara774g@gmail.com)

Vi h√•ber, at I vil v√¶re med til at skabe en smuk og n√¶rv√¶rende film!

De bedste hilsner,

**S√òGER DELTAGERE TIL DOKUMENTAR**

Vi er to filmskabere fra **Potemkin, den jyske filmskole**, der skal til at lave deres afgangsprojekt ‚Äî en smuk, poetisk mini-dokumentar med titlen *Med d√∏den p√• forkant*.

Filmen handler om, hvordan d√∏den kan komme f√∏r tiden ‚Äî og hvordan man lever videre, n√•r nogen forsvinder alt for tidligt. Vi √∏nsker at skabe et stille, √¶rligt og visuelt poetisk portr√¶t af k√¶rligheden og savnet, n√•r livet bliver afbrudt midt i det smukkeste.

For hvordan f√∏les det, n√•r d√∏den kommer p√• forkant?
N√•r man ikke bare savner en person, men ogs√• alt det, personen aldrig n√•ede at opleve?

Vi s√∏ger derfor tre personer, der har oplevet at miste **alt for tidligt**:
* en, der har mistet en **for√¶lder** i en ung alder
* en, der har mistet et **barn**
* og en, der har mistet sin **partner / √¶gtef√¶lle** f√∏r tiden

Optagelserne vil foreg√• i trygge rammer, og vi l√¶gger stor v√¶gt p√• respekt, n√¶rv√¶r og tillid i processen. Vi √∏nsker at skabe en film, der viser sorgen ‚Äì men ogs√• k√¶rligheden, styrken og de sm√• spor, der bliver tilbage.

Hvis du har lyst til at dele din historie ‚Äì eller bare vil h√∏re mere om projektet ‚Äì er du meget velkommen til at skrive til mig p√• denne mail: [sara774g@gmail.com](mailto:sara774g@gmail.com)

Vi h√•ber, at I vil v√¶re med til at skabe en smuk og n√¶rv√¶rende film!

De bedste hilsner, 

Sara Riahi (producer)
Freya Carlsen (instrukt√∏r)

V√¶r med til at lave en f√¶rdig kortfilm p√• en enkelt dag!

‚ÄúTapenade‚Äù er en surrealistisk film workshop, hvor vi med tilf√¶ldighedens kraft og baghovedets sk√∏reste ideer samarbejder om at lave film!

Det er en gratis workshop p√• en enkelt dag, for folk over 15 √•r. Den foreg√•r hos AMOK p√• Rosenkrantzgade 1b, 8000 Aarhus C, l√∏rdag d. 22. november fra kl 12:00-20:00.

Til workshoppen skal vi fordele os ud i forskellige roller; instrukt√∏r, fotograf, lydperson, klipper og skuespiller. 

Hver enkelt person skriver et dogme ned for deres rolle, f.eks; ‚ÄúSkuespilleren skal imitere J√∏rgen Leth‚Äù, ‚ÄúFotografen skal filme som en myre ser verden‚Äù eller ‚ÄúInstrukt√∏ren skal lave en historie om dengang kloakken ved den Permanente fl√∏d over i 1968‚Äù. 

Derefter blander vi det hele, tr√¶kker 5 tilf√¶ldige krav til hver film og g√•r i gang med at skabe filmen i vores grupper!

Om aftenen m√∏des vi og viser filmene til hinanden, samt alle der har lyst til at komme forbi og se dem.

Tilmelding og sp√∏rgsm√•l til siricwf@gmail.com

Instrukt√∏r, fotograf, lydperson, klipper og skuespiller

STARBUCKS COMMERCIAL - SEVERAL STATES.  

OPEN CALL FOR THOSE WHO WOULD LIKE TO APPLY AS LOCALS OR SELF-REPORT TO:

MIAMI, THE HAMPTONS, BALTIMORE, CHICAGO, 
APACHE JUNCTION, OR FAIRBANKS

casting by self tapes, deadline ASAP
MUST SEND SELF TAPE VIDEO WITH AT LEAST ONE OTHER PERSON, CAN BE FAMILY, FRIEND, CO-WORKER, ETC.

SELF TAPE IS SIMPLE
ON VIDEO MODE IN CELLPHONE, SPEAK INTO THE CAMERA, WITH A FRIEND OR FAMILY MEMBER, OR IN GROUPS THAT GET TOGETHER TO ENJOY SOMETHING IN COMMON.

CAN BE ANYTHING. EVERYONE IN THE VIDEO MAKE AN INTRO, AND THEN SPEAK ABOUT WHAT YOU ENJOY GATHERING FOR. 
CAN BE ANYTHING, DOG WALKS, CARD GAMES, CLASSES, MOVIE NIGHTS, BIKER RIDES, FISHING, ANYTHING.

ALL AGES, ALL ETHNICITIES, ALL GENDERS

SEND TO LINK BELOW ASAP.
https://miamitalentcasting.wetransfer.com

WHEN SENDING VIA WETRANSFER, (WHICH IS FREE) 
ADD NAME, LOCATION AND PHONE IN NOTES
SECTION TO BE ABLE TO LOCATE YOU IF BOOKED.

THIS SHOOT NOV 10 AND 12, IN MIAMI, THE REST OF THE STATES WILL SHOOT THE FOLLOWING WEEKS UP UNTIL NOV 17
NO TRAVEL PAID, MUST BE LOCAL OR SELF REPORT.
MAIN $700/10

MAIN buy out ¬∑ $1500
Extras ‚Ä¢ $250/10
Extras Buyout ‚Ä¢ $1,000
Wardrobe ‚Ä¢ $50 for 2 hrs
all rates are -20%af

DEADLINE IS ASAP

Theatre Online Ltd. are still looking for actors to join them for Pantomime 2025. 

This is for PAID, UK Wide school tours. 

Friday 21st November ‚Äì Friday 19th December 2025.

They are ideally looking for drivers aged 25 and above, although the ability to drive is not essential for all roles.

Applicants must have a base in Central Scotland.

They welcome new applications, as well as submissions from previous auditionees and cast members.

For further information go to [www.theatre-online.com/casting](http://www.theatre-online.com/casting?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBEwTkFPTXN5UEczVXJhbUFTSgEeRECCKL3bJvUMs0txOFuVKvAWOD03y0LoKwhZq8wcON8LtGfBqVpfUVmCmHo_aem_Rv0m_fr35reZp5KB25ZnrQ) or email casting@takeawaytheatre.co.uk.

**CASTING CALL - REAL DRAG QUEENS - UNION COMMERCIAL**

**Seeking REAL DRAG QUEENS for a UNION commercial shooting in Vancouver, BC!**

NO ACTING EXPERIENCE REQUIRED!

*OPEN TO UNION & NON-UNION TALENT*

*Must be based in Vancouver/Lower Mainland, BC or be able to work as a local

**To submit for this, please apply via the form below:**

**projecttourist.castingcrane.com**

**SUBMISSION DEADLINE:** November 14, 2025 by 10am PST

**CALLBACKS:** November 20, 2025

**WARDROBE:** December 4, 2025

**RATES:** Per UBCP/ACTRA

**FILMING:** Dec 8-19, 2025, Late January 2026 (Dates TBD) & Late March 2026 (Dates TBD)

BE PREPARED LUZON!  GRABEEE ANG LAKI NG SAKOp!

after Visayas this coming weekend Sunday to Monday
pray for the Philippines ùêÄ ùêåùêéùêçùêíùêìùêÑùêë ùêíùêìùêéùêëùêå ùêàùêí ùêÇùêéùêåùêàùêçùêÜ! üåÄ‚ö†Ô∏è #PrayForThePhilippines

Mabilis pang lumalakas at patuloy na lumalawak ang bagyong may international name na #FungWong at ngayo‚Äôy isa nang Severe Tropical Storm Category, ayon sa Japan Meteorological Agency (JMA).

Taglay na ngayon ng bagyo ang lakas ng hangin na umaabot sa 95 kph at may pagbugso ng hangin na umaabot na sa 130 kph. Kumikilos ang bagyo sa direksyong pa-kanluran sa bilis na 15 kph.

Inaasahang mabilis itong lalakas bilang TYPHOON Category bukas at inaasahang papasok na ng PAR bukas ng gabi o madaling araw ng Sabado at tatawaging #UwanPH.

Bagama‚Äôt patuloy na tinutumbok ng bagyo ang #Northern-#CentralLuzon area, napakalawak ng bagyo kaya inaasahang mararamdaman din ang bagsik nito maging sa #MetroManila, #CALABARZON, #BicolRegion, #MIMAROPA, at maging sa #Visayas.

Patuloy na pinaghahanda ang mga kababayan natin sa mga nabanggit na lugar na paghandaan na po ang paparating na malakas na bagyo. 

HUWAG PO NATING BALEWALAIN ANG MGA PAULIT-ULIT NA MGA BABALA UKOL SA BAGYO DAHIL MALAWAK PO ANG SAKOP NITO.

Manatiling mag-antabay sa mga susunod pang update hinggil sa paparating na bagyo.

PWS/PSU

items.text:
Hello lovely people of "**[Actors Actors Actors! Wanted!](https://www.facebook.com/groups/actorsactors/)****"**

My name is Deborah Rossouw, and I'm a professional photographer and now, a global photography mentor. I wanted to introduce myself and share something new I'm offering.

I've recently launched **"The Visionary Lens," my Global Photography Mentorship program**. This program is designed for anyone passionate about photography ‚Äì from aspiring artists to seasoned professionals ‚Äì looking to truly master their craft, find their unique visual voice, and make a real impact with their images. Through structured teaching and personalized guidance, I help individuals elevate their photography to the next level.

While my mentorship reaches globally, I'm also excited to connect with our local creative community here. Perhaps you've seen some of my advertising, lifestyle, or portraiture work around, or maybe you're just starting your photography journey.

If you or someone you know is keen to develop their photography skills, explore a new artistic direction, or advance their visual career, I invite you to learn more.

You can find all the details about "The Visionary Lens" and how to connect with me here: https://deborahrossouw.myportfolio.com/the-visionary-lens-global-photography-mentor 

Feel free to ask any questions below, and I look forward to contributing to and connecting with our local community!

Warmly,
Deborah Rossouw

items.text:
Hi All, we @northeastproducers are branching out this year. We are testing the water down in the Plymouth, Torquay and Exeter area. We are only doing a short tour, the week commencing 8th of December Monday to Saturday touring our Christmas Panto Jack and The Beanstalk to Care Centers, care homes and extra care schemes, trying to spread a bit of Christmas cheer to those in need of it . We are looking for an actor to play the role of Jack.

If any actors aren't working or have various short contracts on in that period we would love to hear from you.

Fee is 550pw shows are performed between 11am and 3.30pm. A driver is required. All accommodation is sourced for you and paid for by the company and all fuel costs are covered whilst touring. 

If you are interested in working with us please send an email to info@northeastproducers.co.uk

Thanks we look forward to hearing from you :)

Hej alle sammen!

Jeg kommer fra Danmark Radio, hvor vi her i Fakta- og Livsstilsafdelingen sidder og caster til et nyt TV-format. Vi leder efter par, som er i tvivl om, hvorvidt de skal have b√∏rn. 

I en verden med et stigende tempo, t√•rnh√∏je f√∏devarepriser, krig i Europa og klimaangst f√•r vi - som vi er blevet tudet √∏rerne fulde af - f√¶rre b√∏rn end nogensinde. Mere pr√¶cist 1,5 barn i stedet for 2,01 barn pr. Kvinde. For at nuancere problematikken har vi brug for nogle modige medvirkende, som t√∏r lukke os ind i deres tvivl. Er det jer?

I kan h√∏re mange flere detaljer om formatet, hvis I skriver til mig p√• tlf. 50906007 eller nedenfor i kommentarsporet. Jeg vil gl√¶de mig til at tale med jer allesammen :) 

De bedste hilsner

Clara Bruun, journalist, DR Aarhus

items.text:
### Exciting Cast & Crew Call for Indie Short Film Sequel!

Hello all,

I'm thrilled to announce that my screenplay is nearly complete for an indie short film‚Äîa direct sequel to my concept piece, *"The Hollow Concept Short"* (check it out here: ([https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8?si=XUx23izsqJWtl-xT)](https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8?si=XUx23izsqJWtl-xT))). 

This upcoming story dives deep into the aftermath of 'The Hollow,' exploring its haunting progression into our modern world. If you love psychological thrillers with a conceptual twist, this is your chance to be part of something creative and impactful!

This is a **passion-driven, collaborative project** designed as a learning experience for everyone involved. As an indie production, all funds are dedicated towards film gear and post-production‚Äîno salaries, but tons of fun, skill-building, and networking opportunities!

**What We Offer:**

- Lunch on shoot days, a copy of the film and credits

- Hands-on experience in a creative environment

**We're Seeking VOLUNTEER TALENT ONLY‚ÄîUnpaid Roles:**

**Lead Actors (Auditions Required):**

- **Male Lead (Husband Role):** Caucasian, 30-35 years old, slim/athletic build. Must convey emotion, and intensity. This is a starring role with significant screen time!

- **Female Lead (Wife Role):** Caucasian, 29-32 years old, slim/athletic build. Static character, convey emotion and depth with the male lead‚Äîbring your A-game!

*First-time actors are absolutely welcome!* We'll hold tryouts online and discuss roles in detail to ensure the best fit. No prior experience? No problem‚Äîwe're all about promoting growth!

**How to Apply for Acting Roles:**

- Send a wide-shot full-body photo + a close-up headshot.

- Include any reels, clips, or acting samples if available (not required).

- Email applications to [reddybry8films@gmail.com](mailto:reddybry8films@gmail.com) with the subject: "Actor Application - [Role] - [Your Name]".

- Tell us a bit about yourself and why you're excited about this project!

**Supporting Roles & Crew:** 1 PA to help with camera & crew, few minor parts are still in development‚Äîstay tuned for updates, or express interest in your application if you're open to flexibility.

Filming will take place in the Toronto area, with flexible scheduling to accommodate volunteers. Date: tbd, Filming to be done <Dec13

Let's create something memorable together‚Äîapply today and join the journey!

Questions? Reach out via email. Looking forward to your submissions!

Best,  

Bharad Reddy

Writer/Director/Editor

@reddybry8films

topComments.text: Unless it's a student film always pay your cast and crew. Copy, credit and last weeks moldy pizza is not any kind of "offer". You get copy credit and real food on paying jobs so you're not "offering" anything special

thx for pointing out the obvious doesnt matter if student/rookie film, there‚Äôs no producer attached. if u cant help, keep your moldy delusional advice to urself 
thx

**Supporting Roles & Crew:** 1 PA to help with camera & crew, few minor parts are still in development‚Äîstay tuned for updates, or express interest in your application if you're open to flexibility.

Filming will take place in the Toronto area, with flexible scheduling to accommodate volunteers. Date: tbd, Filming to be done <Dec13

Let's create something memorable together‚Äîapply today and join the journey!

Questions? Reach out via email. Looking forward to your submissions!

Best,  

Bharad Reddy

Writer/Director/Editor

items.text:
Casting Call ‚Äì Lead Role ‚ÄúLil Messias‚Äù in Bachelor Film Groupies (The Norwegian Film School) - Paid! 

We are casting for Groupies, an ambitious and visually striking bachelor film by a talented team of students at The Norwegian Film School.

The film explores the groupie phenomenon through a music film about a rapper and a fangirl spending one surreal night backstage. Blending realism, stylization, and surreal imagery, Groupies delves into themes of power, status, gender roles, and what it truly means to be human in a superficial, image-driven world.

Role: Lil Messias (‚ÄúLil Mess‚Äù) ‚Äì Lead
Lil Messias is an internationally acclaimed rap artist.
On stage, he radiates confidence, sex appeal, and dominance ‚Äî the perfect image of modern masculinity.
Beneath the surface, however, he battles growing anxiety and emptiness in a life fueled by drugs, violence, and meaningless sex. He is trapped in his own image and longs to be truly seen. (Age 20-30)

This role involves:
 ‚Ä¢ An intimate scene with the character Ninni.
A professional intimacy coordinator will be attached to ensure a safe, respectful, and transparent process.
 ‚Ä¢ A rap performance, including recording a song and potentially some choreography.
 ‚Ä¢ The creative team will also be developing a full artist brand around the character ‚Äî an exciting opportunity to embody a complete on-screen persona.

Actors of all ethnicities and backgrounds are strongly encouraged to apply.

Production Details
 ‚Ä¢ Shooting period: Between January 20‚Äì30, 2025
 ‚Ä¢ Location: Norway

items.summary:
Casting Call ‚Äì Lead Role ‚ÄúLil Messias‚Äù in Bachelor Film Groupies (The Norwegian Film School) - Paid! 

We are casting for Groupies, an ambitious and visually striking bachelor film by a talented team of students at The Norwegian Film School.

The film explores the groupie phenomenon through a music film about a rapper and a fangirl spending one surreal night backstage. Blending realism, stylization, and surreal imagery, Groupies delves into themes of power, status, gender roles, and what it truly means to be human in a superficial, image-driven world.

Role: Lil Messias (‚ÄúLil Mess‚Äù) ‚Äì Lead
Lil Messias is an internationally acclaimed rap artist.
On stage, he radiates confidence, sex appeal, and dominance ‚Äî the perfect image of modern masculinity.
Beneath the surface, however, he battles growing anxiety and emptiness in a life fueled by drugs, violence, and meaningless sex. He is trapped in his own image and longs to be truly seen. (Age 20-30)

This role involves:
 ‚Ä¢ An intimate scene with the character Ninni.
A professional intimacy coordinator will be attached to ensure a safe, respectful, and transparent process.
 ‚Ä¢ A rap performance, including recording a song and potentially some choreography.
 ‚Ä¢ The creative team will also be developing a full artist brand around the character ‚Äî an exciting opportunity to embody a complete on-screen persona.

Actors of all ethnicities and backgrounds are strongly encouraged to apply.

Production Details
 ‚Ä¢ Shooting period: Between January 20‚Äì30, 2025
 ‚Ä¢ Location: Norway
 ‚Ä¢ Compensation: According to Norwegian industry rates (Tariff)

Travel expenses will be covered.

If this sounds like something for you, please get in touch. Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Email: deteramalie@gmail.com

Thanks so much!

items.text:
Hello everyone! My name is Richelle, my team and I are shooting a short promotional video for our app. Since this is a student-led project we are looking for volunteer actors to join our project!

A little bit about our app, it is designed to help immigrants in the trades industry learn work-related English terms more easily. Our promotional video will be heartfelt and will tell the story of a daughter who sees her mother, a skilled tradeswoman and newcomer to Canada, as her hero. Through hard work, resilience, and learning English, her mother finds her voice in a new country and inspires her daughter to do the same.

Tone: **Emotional, cinematic, and authentic.**

Theme: **Empowerment through language and learning.**

This Christmas at Lower Drayton Farm we are looking for experienced performers in our Jingle Ville. We are looking for joyful Elves, a friendly Mrs Claus and of course a Magical Santa. 

Our Santas grotto experience is like no other and we need you guys to come down and help bring the magic to life. Not only will our customers be able to come and visit Santa they will also get the chance to meet Mrs Claus, watch a Lower Drayton Farm christmas film, have lots of fun doing activities with the Elves and much more! 

The Christmas period will be from the November to 24th December at Play@ Lower Drayton Farm in Penkridge. 

If interested please email play@lowerdraytonfarm.co.uk. Please include your CV, headshot and role you are applying for. We can't wait to hear from you soon!

message.text:
Wow! My new personal record - 91 shows in one month!!!
Back in Norway this September - 60 more shows to come! üí™üèªCatch me on Color Line Fantasy between Oslo and Kiel until October. üö¢ üî•

@anatoliy_bulakh

Male actor, 25-40 years old, wanted.

You should be good-looking and well-built and not afraid of queer parts.

I'm an actor from Germany and from time to time I also make short films, which I present at international film festivals .

My films are arthouse films that may contain nudity and improvisation.

My upcoming short will be an online romance.

The actor should therefore record their part at home using their own smartphone.

Unfortunately, there's no payment, but it only takes 1-2 days. Sorry,  It's not possible to make money with a short film.
Filming will be in English.

I'm also looking for actors for potential future projects.

This is me: www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Please write to Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de

items.text:
Producer and actor perks are still available!
https://www.indiegogo.com/en/projects/talkhardcinema/american-mother-taryn-manning-noel-g-keith-coogan?ref=explore-creator-page
Grab a producer/actor perk on AMERICAN MOTHER. James Duval (INDEPENDENCE DAY, DONNIE DARKO, GONE IN 60 SECONDS, Greg Araki's TEEN APOCALYPSE trilogy) has joined the cast, alongside...
Taryn Manning (ORANGE IS THE NEW BLACK, CROSSROADS, HUSTLE & FLOW, 8 MILE, MEAN GIRLS, SONS OF ANARCHY, THE ITALIAN JOB, CLEVELAND ABDUCTION, COLD MOUNTAIN), Nichole Brown (Aisha from COBRA KAI, RAVEN'S HOME), Keith Coogan (ADVENTURES IN BABYSITTING, TOY SOLDIERS, JAY AND SILENT BOB REBOOT, DON'T TELL MOM THE BABYSITTER'S DEAD, COUSINS) and Noel G. (THE FAST AND THE FURIOUS, FURIOUS 7, TRAINING DAY, STREET KINGS, THE DARK KNIGHT RISES, HARSH TIMES, THE MULE, DRAGGED ACROSS CONCRETE).

All 5 of these actors have already wrapped, so they're definitely a part of the film (no dropping out due to scheduling conflicts, etc). Producers are currently speaking with about several more well known actors in hopes to nab at least 3 of them for the film (maybe 8-10 in total if we can get this campaign to $20k). Grab a producer and actor perk on the film at indiegogo.

And check out our other campaign for THE VICTIM, also featuring James Duval and Noel G. https://www.indiegogo.com/en/projects/talkhardcinema/the-victim?ref=explore-creator-page

Plus AMERICAN SERIAL KILLER, also featuring James Duval and with the addition of Nathan Bexton (Doug Liman's GO, and Gregg Araki's NOWHERE). Producer perks available at https://www.madsincinema.com/investors.html

Title: ‚ÄúBetween Lights and Crossroads‚Äù

The city never really sleeps ‚Äî it just breathes differently at night.
I was on my way home, earphones in, lost in my thoughts, when I saw her again. Same street corner, same caf√© glow painting her face with soft light.

We hadn‚Äôt spoken in months. Life happened ‚Äî silence filled the spaces where words used to live. But in that moment, the noise of the city faded, and all I could hear was the heartbeat I‚Äôd been trying to forget.

She looked up, eyes meeting mine like the world had paused for a second just to remind me that fate doesn‚Äôt ask for permission.
We didn‚Äôt say much. Just a quiet smile, and a simple, ‚ÄúHey, it‚Äôs been a while.‚Äù

Some stories don‚Äôt need an ending.
They just keep breathing ‚Äî somewhere between lights and crossroads.

Open Call In Person Auditions Mon. & Tues. Nov 10 & 11 at 7pm for The 39 Steps by Patrick Barlow, Directed by Liz Bove. Performances: Jan. 9-18: Fri. & Sat. 8pm & Sundays 2pm + 2pm Matinee Sat. 1/17. More Details @ [https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/](https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/) Auditions @HeightsPlayers 26 Willow Place Brooklyn, NY 11201. (718) 237-2752. Please bring a headshot and resume, sides available on website. Please be sure to be available for in person call backs. NO pay.

CHARACTER BREAKDOWN:

**A familiarity with the Hitchcock film, The 39 Steps (1935), is highly recommended as the play is a direct spoof on the film. You may find this on ****[Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jfVtoPN3BVk)****.**
**Richard Hannay:** 30s-40s. A Hitchcock-esque suave, dashing, debonaire fellow. A physically adept comedian. Must be able to do a British accent. 

**Annabella Schmidt:** 20s-30s. An exotic and intriguing spy. Must be able to do a German accent. Actress will also play Margaret. 

**Pamela**: 20s-30s. The quintessential Hitchcock-esqe leading lady. She is bold, emotionally and intellectually intelligent. British accent required. 

**Margaret**: 20s-30s. The wife of a stern religious Scottish farmer. Scottish accent required. Actress will also play Annabella. 

**Clown #1 **& **Clown #2:** Any age, gender, race. Vivacious and debonair, both clowns expertly execute multiple male and female roles with skillful physical comedic skills.  English and Scottish accents a must.

It‚Äôs timeeeeeee! So proud to have put myself out there in order to obtain this opportunity for myself to produce a show with the prestigious 54 Below! All my NYC friends are more than welcome to audition. It‚Äôll be fun! 

‚ÄúStep into the shadows for an unforgettable night of darkly dazzling musical theater. This brand-new cabaret dives into the thrilling worlds of Lizzie: The Rock Musical, The Addams Family, Bat Boy: The Musical, and Sweeney Todd. Featuring a killer cast of powerhouse voices, the evening will blend rock energy, wicked humor, and hauntingly beautiful melodies in a celebration of the darker side of Broadway. Conceived and directed by Gabrielle Dillinger, this electrifying concert invites audiences to embrace the strange, the spooky, and the spectacular. Come experience a night that‚Äôs deliciously twisted and devilishly fun.‚Äù

All auditions due November 27th @11:59PM, with us getting in touch on November 30th.

Performance Date: January 20th, 2026 @9:30PM

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì Z (Main Character)

Project Title:
üé• The Cave

Type:
üéì Student Short Film

Produced by:
University of Edinburgh ECA

Filming Location:
üìç London Road Gardens, Edinburgh (EH7 5EU)

Filming Dates:
üìÖ 11th & 12th November

Work Environment:
‚õ≤Ô∏è Outdoor shoot
üè† Indoor shoot
üçú‚úÖ Meals and refreshments provided
üí∏‚ùå Unpaid project (student production)

‚∏ª

Role:
üé≠ Z (Main Character)
A silent, emotionally expressive character‚Äîno dialogue.
Z‚Äôs world is collapsing quietly within; every tremor, glance, and breath carries weight.

Requirements:
‚Ä¢ Visual Age: around 20
‚Ä¢ Gender: any
‚Ä¢ Strong ability to convey emotion through eyes and body movement
‚Ä¢ Able to express the physicality of anxiety (rigidity, delayed motion, trembling, shifting breath or muscle tone)
‚Ä¢ Comfortable with natural or unkempt makeup (dark circles, oily skin, tired look)

‚ú® Bonus: experience in physical acting or mime, confident with close-ups & long takes

‚∏ª

üïä Performance Note:
Looking for an actor who can bring depth, intensity, and emotional precision through silence.
Subtlety and physical storytelling are key.

‚∏ª

To Apply:
Please send your headshot, CV, Spotlight link (if available), or a short clip showcasing previous performance or introduction.

üìß ecafilmproject@gmail.com
or
üìß 18381437570@163.com

üì∏ Instagram: kabule_kyoku or chloez1142

items.text:
Casting call for a short narrative film **(PAID)**

Hello everyone!

We are looking for three male actors for a short narrative film. See details below:

Film: **Learned Behaviour **

Director:** **Sammy Ofori-Attah** **

Logline: The perfect candidate on paper looks to breeze through their job interview but is it prejudice or their own true nature that becomes the obstacle to their success?

Genre: Psychological drama/Sci-Fi

Shoot Week:** Dates TBC but will fall during: 4th ‚Äì 9th December 2025 (includes 2 day shoot)**

Locations: **London and Watford**

Paid: **¬£166 per day + food and travel expenses** (N.B. Travel within the TFL area covered only)

RAV KOTHARI (Lead, needed two days)

- Asian male, late 20s to early 30s.

- Indian accent required

- The character presents themselves as human but is very much an android

NEIL (Supporting role, needed one day)

- male, late 20s to early 30s.

- Any accent welcome

TED (Supporting role, needed two days)

- White British, male 40s,

- Any UK accent welcome

Audition details: Shortlisted candidates will be contacted for  a self-tape audition.

**Please submit your Spotlight link or CV + headshots and link to your showreel via email to samsanaprod@outlook.com by Thursday 13th November 10 am, stating which role you'd like to apply to.**

Many thanks!

Best,

Susana and Samuel.

the wait is over! we are now accepting submissions for our summer production of ‚ÄúBe More Chill!‚Äù

for full details, visit the link in our bio.

Simone Nathalia - Director/Choreographer
Taylor McKee - Music Director
Madison Raybould - Choreographer
Morgan Da Silva-Rolph - Stage Manager

audition dates
in-person: December 20th & 21st, 2025
callbacks: January 3rd, 2026
self-tapes: submissions due on Dec. 19th

audition venue:
Carousel Theatre for Young People, 1411 Cartwright St, Granville Island

audition requirements:
all roles in this production are volunteer, non-union. xoxo welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and skill levels to audition.

what to prepare:
1. a 32-bar cut of an upbeat musical theatre song in the style of the show.

2. a 1-2 minute contemporary, comedic monologue - this must be memorized.

how to apply:
please email your headshot and resume to theatre@xoxotv.ca to be scheduled with an audition time, or to request a self-tape submission.

character breakdowns can be found in our ‚Äúaudition package‚Äù link in bio.

production dates:
July 15th - 18th, 2026

production venue:
Firehall Arts Centre, 280 E Cordova St, Vancouver

notes:
rehearsals will begin April 30th, 2026
Saturdays 10:00am to 6:00pm
Tuesdays & Thursdays 6:00pm to 10:00pm

contact info@xoxotv.ca or DM us with any questions!

best of luck to all performers - we‚Äôll see you at auditions! üòÅüíÑüêæ

Music and Lyrics by Joe Iconis
Book by Joe Tracz
Based on the Novel by Ned Vizzini

BE MORE CHILL is presented by arrangement with Concord Theatricals.
www.concordtheatricals.com
The world premiere production of Be More Chill was commissioned and originally produced by Two River Theater Company in Red Bank, NJ
John Dias, Artistic Director / Michael Hurst, Managing Director
This work was supported by a Theatre Commissioning and Production Initiative grant from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation
Orchestrations and Arrangements by Charlie Rosen

üì∏ PAID - Model Call: Head Spa Photo & Video Project! üßñ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

NON-UNION

We're looking for a female model to be featured in promotional photos and videos for a head spa in Vancouver! Please do not private message me; submit your application via email at the bottom to be considered.

‚ú®Who We're Looking 

Gender: Female
Hair Colour: Brunette (must have naturally dark or dyed brown hair)
Ages: 25-45 (approximate, flexible for the right fit)
Look: Must be comfortable being filmed enjoying a head spa treatment (head spa service only). A naturally serene, elegant, and refreshed look is key.

üé•Project Details
Location: Vancouver

Date: Currently planning for the last week of November; the exact date will be confirmed in advance.

Duration: 2 hours max

Acting experience: beneficial, but not required; no dialogue in the video
Content: Photos and video to be used on the client‚Äôs website and social media (Facebook/Instagram).
Compensation: Complimentary spa services during filming + your hourly rate.

How to Apply

If you're interested and fit the criteria, please send us:
1. A brief video introduction about yourself and why you'd be a great fit.
2. Your hourly rate.
3. If you have acting experience, your demo reel or links to the latest acting projects
4. 3-5 recent, clear, non-filtered photos (at least one close-up and one full-body shot).
5. Your availability for the last two weeks of November, including days and times

üìß Email your submission to casting@wildlyvisual.com with the subject line "Vancouver Head Spa Model Call."

==============================

F√ºr einen Bewerbungsfilm an der DFFB, der sich mit dem Thema ‚ÄûSehnsucht‚Äú auseinandersetzt, wird ein Schauspieler gesucht.

 

Der Film ist im Wesentlichen eine Neuinterpretation eines ber√ºhmten DFFB-Kurzfilms aus dem Jahr 1968, in dem eine rote Fahne von mehreren Personen durch die Stra√üen West-Berlins getragen wird. In unserer Version tr√§gt eine einzelne, verkleidete Person nacheinander verschiedene Flaggen.

 

Geplant ist ein Drehtag bzw. ein halber Drehtag, voraussichtlich Mitte November.

 

Eine Mappe mit weiteren Informationen zu Ablauf, Drehort usw. steht bereits zur Verf√ºgung. Die Teilnahme ist ehrenamtlich, bietet aber die M√∂glichkeit, Seterfahrung bei einem spannenden und humorvollen Projekt zu sammeln.

items.text:
The International Conference "Performing Arts Between Tradition & Contemporaneity" was founded in 2003 to create a space for serious dialogue between traditional performance practices and contemporary artistic innovation. 

Over 22 editions, it has become a respected gathering point for performing arts professionals worldwide who refuse to see tradition and innovation as opposing forces, but rather as complementary elements in a living, evolving artistic practice.

Dates: December 18-22, 2025

Location: Schloss Laubegg, Austria

Capacity: Approximately 50 participants

Read More: https://www.nipai.org/post/22nd-performing-arts-conference  .

sharedPost.text:
Atomic Theatre Wheat Ridge CO, presents:

Reading With The Rabbits a two-part youth theatre program designed to nurture young performers and inspire a love of literacy in the community.

Part One: Tween & Teen Performers
We provide tween and teen actors with a platform to showcase their character work, voice acting, and stage presence in front of a live audience. Using picture books as the medium, performers present their own directorial vision of a story of their choosing. Each show features 4‚Äì5 different stories, ensemble songs, and theatre games.

In a world where teen actors are often limited by age, gender, physical type, or busy school and sports schedules, Reading with the Rabbits offers a flexible, creative space to experiment and play.

Upcoming Auditions

Date: December 10

Time: 6-8PM

Location: Wheat Ridge Grange 

Performances: Saturday December13 at 1:30 and 3:30 

Theme: Winter 
J√≥lab√≥kafl√≥√∞i√∞ (book flood)

Actors will be given a stipend for their time. 

Audition Prep: reserve an audition time slot by emailing atomictheatre@gmail.com 

Actors are expected  to come with a performance ready picture  book to entertain young children and their families. Be perpared to show the book during  your staged reading.  You are the director/ actor and MC. Show off your different characters, find games within the pages, incorporate music or movement, break the fourth wall and invite the audience into your imagination. 

We appreciate your creativity and attention to detail, and can‚Äôt wait to experience your theatrical offering.

Be prepared to learn a sing-along song, minor choreography, and an improv game that will be played with the ensemble during the performances

Part Two: Community Story Hours
These donation-based performances are free and open to the public. Each event features:

Storytime performances where new readers watch older kids bring books to life.

Photo opportunities

Themed crafts to make the experience extra engaging for families.

* Usually bunnies who demonstrate how to be good audience members with their listening ears.  Our December showcase will be around a bonfire at a local urban farm weather permitting. The goats and chickens will be standing in for the rabbits.

items.text:
Howdy Denver film community! We‚Äôre Wasteland of Wonder, a boutique film production company based here in Denver, CO that focuses on community building through creative collaboration. We‚Äôre seeking an actor for a music video and would love to engage with some new, local talent. Email us at wastelandofwonder@gmail.com for information about auditions!

TITLE: ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt Think‚Äù 

GENRE: Gothic industrial music video 

SYNOPSIS: ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt Think‚Äù explores themes of control and alienation both societally and personally with evocative and surreal imagery.  Our protagonist, Ezra, is an audience member at a surrealist concert- who slowly loses themself in the music. In a B plot we see manufacturers, men in a unique blend of industrial and medical garb, grooming and preparing Ezra for some kind of operation.  

CHARACTER: Ezra, (20s), feels alienated and unable to connect with others.  Ezra‚Äôs arc in the video is one of surrender and vulnerability, giving in to the pressures of everyone around them. 

This role is open casting for Men and Nonbinary actors of any race. Ideally the actor would be very skilled in physical work and have a dramatic background. 

PRODUCTION INFO

PRODUCTION COMPANY: Wasteland of Wonder (wastelandofwonder.com)

PRODUCTION TYPE: Music Video

CONTACT INFO: wastelandofwonder@gmail.com

COMPENSATION: The role will be compensated, rate TBD 

AUDITION INFORMATION: No audition, just send us a resume and reel :). Email us for further information. 

SHOOT SCHEDULE: Mid November 

FILMING LOCATION: Denver Metro & the Front Range

CASTING CALL: Protesters Voiceover ‚Äì ‚ÄúDenied Care‚Äù Series

Project Title: Denied Care
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment, Inc.
Type: Voiceover (Non-Union / Indie Production)
Location: Remote Recording Accepted
Compensation: paid 
Recording Date: November 15th

Looking for 3 voiceovers

---

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Denied Care is a scripted drama following Ava Winters, a young woman denied life-saving treatment by a broken healthcare system. The story exposes the real human cost of bureaucratic neglect through emotional, defiant, and darkly comedic storytelling.

Short Film feature a pivotal protest montage ‚Äî where voices from across the nation rise in solidarity. This casting call is for those protester voices ‚Äî raw, real, and unapologetic.

---

ROLE: PROTESTER VOICEOVER (MULTIPLE TALENTS)

Gender: Any
Age Range: 18‚Äì65
Accent: Open ‚Äî diverse voices encouraged
Tone: Authentic, passionate, emotional, and real
Vocal Quality:

Gritty, tired, but determined

Feels like you‚Äôve lived it ‚Äî not ‚Äúperformed‚Äù it

Think real activists, not voice actors

Examples of Lines (for audition):

‚ÄúWe are not invisible!‚Äù

‚ÄúYou can‚Äôt deny care to the living!‚Äù

‚ÄúWe‚Äôre sick, not silent!‚Äù

‚ÄúEvery denial has a name!‚Äù

‚ÄúWe are the denied ‚Äî and we‚Äôre not backing down!‚Äù

(Actors may be asked to record crowd-style chants, overlapping dialogue, and emotional reactions.)

---

RECORDING NOTES

Please record clean audio (WAV or MP3) with minimal background noise.

Multiple takes with varying energy levels are encouraged.

Shouting, chanting, and overlapping crowd energy welcome.

Hi All, we @northeastproducers are branching out this year. We are testing the water down in the Plymouth, Torquay and Exeter area. We are only doing a short tour, the week commencing 8th of December Monday to Saturday touring our Christmas Panto Jack and The Beanstalk to Care Centers, care homes and extra care schemes, trying to spread a bit of Christmas cheer to those in need of it . We are looking for an actor to play the role of Jack.

If any actors aren't working or have various short contracts on in that period we would love to hear from you.

Fee is 550pw shows are performed between 11am and 3.30pm. A driver is required. All accommodation is sourced for you and paid for by the company and all fuel costs are covered whilst touring. 

If you are interested in working with us please send an email to info@northeastproducers.co.uk

Thanks we look forward to hearing from you :)

Schauspieler gesucht!

F√ºr ein Studentenprojektfilm suchen wir Freiwillige
die gerne Schauspielerisch vor die Kamera treten
wollen.
Aber erstmal: Wer sind wvir?
Wir sind eine Gruppe aus 4 Studenten des
Studiengangs "Film und Media Arts" der
Hochschule Flensburg.

Unser Ziel:
Als Pr√ºfungsleistung des Moduls "Kurzfilmprojekt
4" m√∂chten wir einen ca. 20 Min√ºtigen
Kom√∂dien-Kurzspielfilm drehen, der auch auf
Filmfestivals laufen soll.

Worum soll es im Film gehen?
Tobias , unser Hauptcharakter, befindet sich in
einer Misslichen Lage. Seitdem er einmal am Tag
seines Vorstellungsgespr√§ches verschlafen hat,
ger√§t er in eine Zeitschleife. In der durchlebt den
selben Tag immer und immer wieder. Und egal was
er auch tut, jedes Mal schafft er es nicht, p√ºnktlich
zum Vorstellungsgespr√§ch seiner Wunschfirma
zu kommen. Mit jeder Verbesserung alter Fehler
kommen neue Hinternisse hinzu.

F√ºr welche Rollen brauchen wir dich?

Zum einen:
m√§nnlich, 20-38 Jahre alt
f√ºr die Rolle des Tobias
(5-9 Drehtage)

Zum anderen:
weiblich, 50-70 Jahre alt
f√ºr die Rolle der Nachbarin
(1-2 Drehtage)

Und noch:
weiblich/m√§nnlich/divers, 20-50 Jahre alt
f√ºr die Rolle des/r Sekret√§r*in
(1 Drehtag)

Zum Dreh:
Drehen w√ºrden wir haupts√§chlich in Flensburg und
Umgebung, aber auch im Kreis-Eckernf√∂rde.
Wenn du also aus Schleswig-Holstein kommst,
w√§re das nat√ºrlich leichter.
Die Maximal 9 Drehtage finden irgendwann
zwischen der 2.Januarwoche und Ende Februar
2026 statt.
Den Zeitraum haben wir bewusst flexibler
gestellt, um sie mit den Terminen des
Hauptrollenschauspielers passender und leichter

planen zu k√∂nnen.
Catering ist nat√ºrlich inklusive
Hast du Interesse und keine Scheu vor der Kamera
zU spielen?

Schauspielerfahrungen (ob Profi oder Schultheater)
w√§ren sch√∂n, sind aber nicht zwingend notwendig.
Und reicht es wenn du mit Spass, Kreativit√§t und
Freude dabei bist.

Reiche deine Bewerbungen ein bei:

Email:mige7636@stud.hs-flensburg.de

oder schreib mich einfach √ºber diesen Account an

Wir freuen uns auf Dich!
